---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Explore the Airport"
  description="54CL Lake Riverside Estates Airport — runway info, guest access, and pilot essentials for Fly LRE."
  current="explore"
>
  <div class="page page-wide">
    <header class="hero hero-compact">
      <p class="hero-eyebrow">54CL · Lake Riverside Estates</p>
      <h1>Explore the Airport</h1>
      <p class="hero-tagline">Adventure Begins at the End of the Runway.</p>
    </header>

    <section>
      <p>
        <strong>54CL</strong> is the private runway at the heart of a fly-in community — built for
        pilots who live here and the friends they bring to the field.
      </p>
      <p>
        Visitors welcome with prior permission from residents. Before you fly in, please take a
        moment to review the <a href="#airport-rules">airport rules</a> and
        <a href="#airport-diagram">airport diagram</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Quick Reference</h2>
      <div class="spec-grid">
        <div class="spec-item">
          <span class="spec-label">Identifier</span>
          <span class="spec-value">54CL (private use)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-item">
          <span class="spec-label">Location</span>
          <span class="spec-value">Aguanga, CA</span>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-item">
          <span class="spec-label">Coordinates</span>
          <span class="spec-value">N33°31.30′ / W116°47.76′</span>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-item">
          <span class="spec-label">Elevation</span>
          <span class="spec-value">~3,410′ MSL</span>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-item">
          <span class="spec-label">Runway</span>
          <span class="spec-value">10/28 · ~3,500′ paved</span>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-item">
          <span class="spec-label">CTAF</span>
          <span class="spec-value"><a href="#ctaf">122.9</a></span>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-item">
          <span class="spec-label">Fuel / Services</span>
          <span class="spec-value">None</span>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-item">
          <span class="spec-label">Airport Diagram</span>
          <span class="spec-value"><a href="#airport-diagram">View diagram</a></span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div id="ctaf" class="ctaf-guide">
        <h3>CTAF (122.9)</h3>
        <p>
          Announce position and intentions on <strong>122.9</strong>. You can also key the mic
          briefly on frequency for automated services:
        </p>
        <ul class="rules-list">
          <li><strong>3 clicks</strong> — abbreviated weather</li>
          <li><strong>4 clicks</strong> — full weather report</li>
          <li><strong>5 clicks</strong> — pilot-controlled runway lighting</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="airport-diagram">
      <h2>Airport Diagram</h2>
      <figure class="airport-diagram">
        <img
          src="/images/54CL-Diagram.jpg"
          alt="54CL airport diagram — Runway 10/28, visitor tie-downs, pattern altitude 4400 feet, CTAF 122.9, departures, and nearby obstructions"
          width="908"
          height="545"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <figcaption>
          Drawing not to scale. Directions, elevations, and positional information are approximate.
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

    <section id="airport-rules">
      <h2>Airport Rules</h2>
      <p>
        Lake Riverside Estates Airport is an FAA restricted private-use airport, preserved for
        property owners and guests of Lake Riverside Estates. Information regarding this airport is
        voluntarily supplied by the LRE Pilots&rsquo; Association. Strict adherence to all
        regulations promulgated by the FAA and the California Department of Aviation, as well as
        compliance with the LRE Airport Conditional Use Permit, is required.
      </p>
      <p>
        The LRE Pilots&rsquo; Association is keenly interested in maintaining a safe, responsible,
        and considerate flying community. We recognize that the LRE Airport is of significant benefit
        to the local community and to those LRE property owners who have invested significant time,
        money, and energy in establishing and maintaining the airport. We petition you, the pilot,
        to respect this investment and cooperate with us in maintaining good-neighbor policies with
        our non-flying LRE area residents.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="airport-procedures">
      <h2>Field Procedures</h2>
      <ul class="rules-list">
        <li>Departing traffic use full runway length.</li>
        <li>Do not park on runway — maintain 75&rsquo; behind runway lights.</li>
        <li>
          Guest aircraft use any unreserved tie-down in the visitor tie-down area, and must supply
          their own straps, chains, or rope.
        </li>
        <li>Displaced threshold — both ends.</li>
        <li>All concrete aprons and tie-downs are private.</li>
        <li>Ditches and runway lights — both sides.</li>
        <li>No fuel or transportation available.</li>
        <li>Calm wind runway is <strong>10</strong>.</li>
        <li>Announce position and intentions on CTAF (<a href="#ctaf">122.9</a>).</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="spec-grid">
        <div class="spec-item">
          <span class="spec-label">Field elevation</span>
          <span class="spec-value">3,410&rsquo; MSL</span>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-item">
          <span class="spec-label">Runway</span>
          <span class="spec-value">10/28 · 3,500&rsquo; × 75&rsquo; paved, lighted</span>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-item spec-item-wide">
          <span class="spec-label">Caution</span>
          <span class="spec-value">Low-level military training in area</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="note">
        Directions, elevations, and positional information are approximate. Procedures based on LRE
        Pilots&rsquo; Association information sheet (rev 09/20/23), updated for current paved runway.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Association Regulations</h2>
      <p>
        Excerpt from Lake Riverside Estates Community Association Rules and Regulations (10-15-05).
        Lake Riverside Estates Airport is an FAA restricted private-use airport solely for use by
        LRE members and their guests. (CC&amp;Rs p. 22)
      </p>
      <ol class="rules-list rules-list-numbered">
        <li>
          All aircraft using the runway and designated parking areas must be insured for liability
          and property damage.
        </li>
        <li>
          All pilots using the airstrip must be licensed, where required by the FAA, and meet all
          FAA requirements for piloting their aircraft.
        </li>
        <li>
          All aircraft using the tie-down areas must be no more than six months out of annual
          inspection. The Association has the right to remove non-compliant or abandoned aircraft
          from the tie-down area at the owner&rsquo;s expense.
        </li>
        <li>No aircraft may park on the runway or within 75&rsquo; of the edge of the runway.</li>
        <li>
          Nothing shall be constructed or placed within the &ldquo;Object Free Zone&rdquo; in
          accordance with policies set forth by the FAA.
        </li>
        <li>
          Aircraft not housed or tied down at a residence adjacent to the airport or in the
          designated tie-down areas must be towed to and from the airport.
        </li>
        <li>
          All pilots utilizing the airport should review this information and procedures page.
          Copies are also available at the association office or from members of the Lake Riverside
          Estates Airport Committee.
        </li>
        <li>All aircraft using the runway must be equipped for two-way radio communication.</li>
        <li>
          All pilots using the runway must announce their intentions on <strong>122.9</strong> before
          taking the runway, entering the pattern, or back-taxiing.
        </li>
        <li>All pilots must follow the appropriate traffic pattern.</li>
        <li>
          Members must be present to meet their guests as they arrive, or provide a letter of
          authorization.
        </li>
        <li>
          No parking on a private lot adjacent to the runway is permitted unless invited by the
          owner.
        </li>
        <li>No touch-and-goes are allowed.</li>
        <li>
          When departing, pilots should use the best angle of climb and be noise sensitive at all
          times. Calm wind runway is <strong>10</strong>.
        </li>
        <li>No unauthorized vehicles or persons are permitted on the runway.</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="cta-box">
        <p><strong>Guest aircraft parking</strong></p>
        <p>
          Guests of LRE property owners may park in the designated transient parking area for not
          more than <strong>30 consecutive days</strong> in a twelve-month period from the first day
          the aircraft arrives. Any longer stay requires written board approval (revised August 15,
          2015).
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Flying In</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Private airfield — LRE residents and their guests only</li>
        <li>Check windsocks (midfield and east end) for Runway 10 vs 28</li>
        <li>Confirm runway status before departure — watch for threshold <strong>X</strong> markings during maintenance</li>
        <li>Noise-sensitive departures; transient tie-downs on the west end (Runway 10)</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Airspace &amp; Weather</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Class G</strong> surrounds the field — stay aware of nearby Class B, C, and D
        airspace within roughly 15 nm. The valley location at ~3,400′ MSL delivers
        <strong>340+ VFR days</strong> a year, often above coastal fog and smog. Plan
        performance accordingly on hot days.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>The Field</h2>
      <p>
        Paved runway with run-up areas at both ends. Runway lighting and VASI on Runway 28.
        This is not an airport near a neighborhood — the runway <em>is</em> the neighborhood.
        Fly-in homes, tie-downs, a private lake, trails, and a clubhouse shared by the community.
      </p>
      <p>
        Respect quiet hours, neighbors, and the field everyone shares.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Nearby</h2>
      <div class="spec-grid">
        <div class="spec-item">
          <span class="spec-label">By air</span>
          <span class="spec-value">~9 min → French Valley (F70) — fuel, FBO, wine country</span>
        </div>
        <div class="spec-item">
          <span class="spec-label">By car</span>
          <span class="spec-value">~24 min → Temecula · ~10 min → Anza</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="cta-box">
      <p><strong>Planning a visit?</strong></p>
      <p>
        Visitors welcome with prior permission from residents. Before you fly in, please take a
        moment to review the <a href="#airport-rules">airport rules</a> and
        <a href="#airport-diagram">airport diagram</a> on this page.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
